A constructor is a set of instructions which can be used for initialization of variables and for instantiation(object creation).
The name of a constructor must be same as of the class. There is no return type in the constructor.
It is of two types i) default constructor ii) custom constructor
default constructors are created on their own in a class if a custom const. is not defined.
A custom const. is a user-defined const. it can be of two types.
a) A non-parameterized const. which do not accept any arguments as they dont have any parameters.
b) parameterized const. which accepts arguments as they have one or more parameters.
